        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Since the getMagicFile() method was modified to check if some magicfile exists in most current places like \"\/usr\/share\/...\", I get warnings due to open basedir restriction on my hosting provider.\r\nIt's due to the file_exists() method, I guess...\r\n\r\nIs it possible to deactivate that or anything ?\r\n\r\nTypical error I get :\r\n<b>Warning<\/b>:  file_exists() [<a href='function.file-exists'>function.file-exists<\/a>]: open_basedir restriction in effect. File(\/usr\/share\/misc\/magic) is not within the allowed path(s): (\/home\/www\/4c4a9afbc958438a3a92ddffa0303afc:\/tmp:\/opt\/php\/lib\/php) in <b>\/home\/www\/4c4a9afbc958438a3a92ddffa0303afc\/data\/lib\/zend_framework_196\/library\/Zend\/Validate\/File\/MimeType.php<\/b> on line <b>144<\/b><br \/>\r\n"
        },
